---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { url } from '../../utils/url';
import FAQSection from '../../components/FAQSection.astro';

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'Can I really generate leads without Google or Meta ads?',
    answer: 'Yes — and many startups should. Google and Meta aren\'t the only platforms with buyers, and they\'re often the most expensive. LinkedIn organic, Bing Ads, Reddit Ads, newsletter sponsorships, and SEO content can all generate qualified leads at lower cost. The key is matching channels to your audience. B2B SaaS companies often find LinkedIn organic and Bing outperform Meta by 3-5x on cost per qualified lead.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What\'s the minimum budget to test alternative ad platforms?',
    answer: 'You can run meaningful tests on most alternative platforms for $500-$1,000/month. Reddit and Quora both have low minimum spends and CPCs under $1. Bing Ads can be tested with $500/month. Newsletter sponsorships start at $200-$500 per placement. The key is testing one platform at a time with enough budget to reach statistical significance — usually 2-4 weeks of consistent spend.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How long does organic marketing take to generate leads?',
    answer: 'SEO content typically takes 3-6 months to rank and drive consistent organic traffic. LinkedIn organic can generate leads within weeks if you already have a network. Email marketing from an existing list can drive results immediately. The compounding effect is what makes organic powerful: a blog post you write today will generate leads for years. Paid stops the moment you stop paying.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Should I stop Google and Meta ads entirely?',
    answer: 'Not necessarily — the goal is to reduce dependency, not eliminate useful channels. If Google Ads are profitable for your business, keep running them. But diversify. Allocate 20-30% of your paid budget to alternative platforms, and invest in organic channels that build owned assets. The companies that thrive long-term are the ones that don\'t rely on any single channel for more than 30-40% of their leads.',
  },
];
---

<Layout
  title="How to Get Leads Without Expensive Google and Meta Ads — Jodie Plant Marketing"
  description="Alternative lead generation strategies: cheaper ad platforms (Bing, Reddit, Quora), organic channels, and budget examples at $2K, $3K, and $5K/month."
>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="bg-navy text-white py-16 sm:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-orange font-mono text-sm font-semibold mb-4">Marketing Guide</p>
        <h1 class="font-headline text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold leading-tight">
          How to Get Leads Without Expensive Google and Meta Ads
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-white/70 leading-relaxed">
          You can generate qualified leads without spending heavily on Google and Meta by using cheaper ad platforms like Bing (60% lower CPCs), Reddit ($0.20 CPCs), and Quora ($0.35-$0.75 CPCs), combined with organic channels like LinkedIn content, SEO, newsletter sponsorships, and community marketing. The smart-stack approach diversifies your spend across platforms where your competitors aren't driving up costs.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MAIN CONTENT -->
  <section class="py-16 sm:py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">

        <h2 class="font-headline text-3xl font-bold text-navy">Why CPCs Keep Climbing (and Won't Stop)</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-text leading-relaxed">
          Google Ads average CPC for B2B keywords has risen 15-20% year over year since 2022. In competitive SaaS categories, you're looking at $8-$25 per click — and that's before factoring in the 3-5% of clicks that actually convert. Meta isn't much better: average CPCs for B2B have climbed past $3-$5, with CPMs up 30% in the last two years.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-text leading-relaxed">
          The reason is simple: more advertisers are competing for the same inventory. Google and Meta are mature platforms. Every SaaS company, every agency, every startup in your space is bidding on the same keywords and targeting the same audiences. When everyone goes to the same auction, prices go up.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-text leading-relaxed">
          That doesn't mean Google and Meta are dead. They still work — but they're no longer the default efficient choice they once were. Smart marketers are building "smart stacks" — diversified lead generation systems that combine cheaper paid alternatives with organic channels that build compounding assets.
        </p>

        <!-- ALTERNATIVE PAID PLATFORMS -->
        <h2 class="font-headline text-3xl font-bold text-navy mt-16">Alternative Paid Platforms (with Real CPC Data)</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-text leading-relaxed">
          These platforms have real buyers on them. They just don't have the same advertiser competition — yet. That's your window.
        </p>

      </div>

      <!-- PLATFORM CARDS -->
      <div class="mt-10 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 max-w-4xl">

        <div class="bg-light rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-100">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
            <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-navy">Bing / Microsoft Ads</h3>
            <span class="font-mono text-sm font-bold text-orange bg-orange/10 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">~60% lower CPC</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Bing captures 9% of US search market — that's tens of millions of searches daily. The audience skews professional, older, and higher-income (enterprise IT, finance, healthcare). B2B advertisers routinely see 40-60% lower CPCs than Google for identical keywords.
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-1 text-sm text-text">
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-orange">&#10003;</span> Import Google Ads campaigns directly (takes 10 minutes)</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-orange">&#10003;</span> LinkedIn profile targeting built-in (job title, company, industry)</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-orange">&#10003;</span> Lower competition = lower cost per lead in most B2B categories</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-muted"><strong class="text-navy">Best for:</strong> B2B SaaS, enterprise, finance, healthcare. Any industry where buyers use desktop search.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-light rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-100">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
            <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-navy">Reddit Ads</h3>
            <span class="font-mono text-sm font-bold text-orange bg-orange/10 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">~$0.20 CPC</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Reddit's 52M+ daily active users organize into highly specific communities (subreddits) by interest, profession, and industry. CPC averaging $0.20-$0.50 makes it one of the cheapest paid traffic sources available. The audience is engaged and research-oriented — they're actively looking for solutions.
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-1 text-sm text-text">
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-orange">&#10003;</span> Target by subreddit (e.g., r/SaaS, r/startups, r/smallbusiness)</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-orange">&#10003;</span> Conversation ads blend into the platform naturally</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-orange">&#10003;</span> CPCs 5-10x lower than Google for similar audiences</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-muted"><strong class="text-navy">Best for:</strong> Tech products, developer tools, SaaS. Audiences that hang out in niche communities.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-light rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-100">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
            <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-navy">Quora Ads</h3>
            <span class="font-mono text-sm font-bold text-orange bg-orange/10 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">$0.35&ndash;$0.75 CPC</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Quora users are in active research mode — they're asking and answering questions about products, tools, and solutions. This makes the intent quality exceptionally high. CPCs run $0.35-$0.75, with strong conversion rates because users are already problem-aware.
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-1 text-sm text-text">
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-orange">&#10003;</span> Target by topic, question, or interest</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-orange">&#10003;</span> High-intent audience actively researching solutions</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-orange">&#10003;</span> Answer-based ads feel organic and build trust</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-muted"><strong class="text-navy">Best for:</strong> B2B services, consulting, SaaS, education. Products that solve questions people actually ask.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-light rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-100">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
            <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-navy">TikTok Spark Ads</h3>
            <span class="font-mono text-sm font-bold text-orange bg-orange/10 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">$0.50&ndash;$2.00 CPC</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Spark Ads amplify existing organic content — yours or a creator's — as paid ads. They feel native, perform better than traditional display, and can reach niche professional audiences. B2B TikTok is real: founder-led content regularly drives leads for tech companies.
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-1 text-sm text-text">
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-orange">&#10003;</span> Amplify organic content that's already performing</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-orange">&#10003;</span> Strong engagement metrics (views, shares, comments)</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-orange">&#10003;</span> B2B audience is growing rapidly (especially founder/startup content)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-muted"><strong class="text-navy">Best for:</strong> Consumer products, DTC brands, and B2B companies with founder-led content strategies.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-light rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-100 md:col-span-2">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
            <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-navy">Pinterest Ads</h3>
            <span class="font-mono text-sm font-bold text-orange bg-orange/10 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">$0.10&ndash;$1.50 CPC</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Pinterest is a visual search and discovery engine with 480M+ monthly active users. The audience is heavily purchase-intent — 85% of weekly Pinners have bought something based on Pins they saw. CPCs are remarkably low, and Pins have a long shelf life (unlike social posts that die in 24 hours, Pins drive traffic for months).
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-muted"><strong class="text-navy">Best for:</strong> E-commerce, design services, home/lifestyle brands, agencies with visual portfolios, and any B2C product with strong visual appeal.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="max-w-3xl mt-16">

        <!-- ORGANIC ALTERNATIVES -->
        <h2 class="font-headline text-3xl font-bold text-navy">Organic Lead Generation Channels</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-text leading-relaxed">
          Paid alternatives reduce your cost per lead. Organic channels reduce it to near-zero over time — because you're building assets you own, not renting attention you have to keep paying for.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-10 space-y-8">
          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-1 bg-orange rounded-full"></div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy text-lg">LinkedIn Organic Content</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-text leading-relaxed">
                LinkedIn's organic reach in 2026 is still dramatically better than any other social platform for B2B. A founder or marketing leader posting 3-4 times per week can realistically reach 10,000-50,000 impressions per month — for free. The key is consistency and substance: share real insights, real data, real stories. Not generic "10 tips" posts.
              </p>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted">
                <strong class="text-navy">Expected results:</strong> 5-15 qualified inbound leads per month within 90 days of consistent posting. Higher for companies with existing networks.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-1 bg-orange rounded-full"></div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy text-lg">Micro-Influencer Partnerships</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-text leading-relaxed">
                Forget celebrity influencers. B2B micro-influencers — newsletter authors, podcast hosts, LinkedIn creators with 5,000-50,000 followers — charge $100-$500 per post and deliver hyper-targeted reach to the exact audience you want. A single sponsored post from a respected voice in your niche can outperform $2,000 in ad spend.
              </p>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted">
                <strong class="text-navy">Typical cost:</strong> $100-$500 per sponsored post or mention. ROI is highest when the influencer genuinely uses or believes in your product.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-1 bg-orange rounded-full"></div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy text-lg">Newsletter Sponsorships</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-text leading-relaxed">
                Niche B2B newsletters have highly engaged audiences that actually read them. Sponsoring a newsletter with 5,000-20,000 subscribers typically costs $200-$1,000 per placement and delivers warm, targeted traffic. Unlike ads, newsletter sponsorships come with implied endorsement from a trusted source.
              </p>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted">
                <strong class="text-navy">Where to find them:</strong> SparkLoop, Swapstack, or direct outreach to newsletters your target audience reads. Test 3-5 different newsletters with small placements before committing to recurring sponsorships.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-1 bg-orange rounded-full"></div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy text-lg">Community Marketing</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-text leading-relaxed">
                Slack communities, Discord servers, industry forums, and Reddit communities are where your buyers hang out and ask for recommendations. Being genuinely helpful in these spaces — answering questions, sharing expertise, contributing to discussions — builds trust that converts to leads without a dollar of ad spend.
              </p>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted">
                <strong class="text-navy">The catch:</strong> This takes time and can't be faked. Community marketing rewards authenticity and punishes self-promotion. The companies that win here are the ones whose team members genuinely participate, not just sell.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-1 bg-orange rounded-full"></div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy text-lg">Podcast Advertising</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-text leading-relaxed">
                Niche B2B podcasts with 1,000-10,000 listeners per episode charge $500-$2,000 per episode for host-read ads. The CPM looks expensive compared to digital display, but podcast listeners trust host recommendations at a rate that dwarfs any other medium. Conversion rates from podcast ads are typically 2-5x higher than display.
              </p>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted">
                <strong class="text-navy">Pro tip:</strong> Start with podcasts your founder or team already listens to. Guest appearances (free) can be even more effective than paid sponsorships.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-1 bg-orange rounded-full"></div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy text-lg">SEO &amp; Content Marketing</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-text leading-relaxed">
                The highest-ROI marketing channel over any 12+ month period. A single well-optimized blog post targeting a high-intent keyword can drive 500-5,000 visits per month indefinitely — with zero ongoing cost. The investment is upfront (research, writing, optimization), but the returns compound for years.
              </p>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted">
                <strong class="text-navy">Timeline:</strong> 3-6 months to see meaningful organic traffic. 6-12 months to build a reliable organic lead pipeline. Worth every day of the wait.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- SMART-STACK BUDGET EXAMPLES -->
        <h2 class="font-headline text-3xl font-bold text-navy mt-16">Smart-Stack Budget Examples</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-text leading-relaxed">
          Here's how to allocate a marketing budget across these channels at different spend levels. These are starting frameworks — the exact mix should be tuned based on your industry, audience, and performance data.
        </p>

      </div>

      <!-- BUDGET STACKS -->
      <div class="mt-10 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 max-w-4xl">

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-6">
          <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-navy">$2,000/mo Stack</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted mt-1">Bootstrapped / early seed</p>
          <div class="mt-6 space-y-3">
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm py-2 border-b border-gray-100">
              <span class="text-text">SEO content (2 posts)</span>
              <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-navy">$800</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm py-2 border-b border-gray-100">
              <span class="text-text">Bing Ads</span>
              <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-navy">$500</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm py-2 border-b border-gray-100">
              <span class="text-text">Reddit Ads</span>
              <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-navy">$300</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm py-2 border-b border-gray-100">
              <span class="text-text">Newsletter sponsorship (1x)</span>
              <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-navy">$400</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-muted"><strong class="text-navy">Strategy:</strong> Build organic foundation while testing the two cheapest paid channels. One newsletter placement per month for immediate reach.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border-2 border-orange p-6 relative">
          <span class="absolute -top-3 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 bg-orange text-white text-xs font-bold px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Recommended</span>
          <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-navy">$3,000/mo Stack</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted mt-1">Seed to Series A</p>
          <div class="mt-6 space-y-3">
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm py-2 border-b border-gray-100">
              <span class="text-text">SEO content (3 posts)</span>
              <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-navy">$1,200</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm py-2 border-b border-gray-100">
              <span class="text-text">Bing Ads</span>
              <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-navy">$600</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm py-2 border-b border-gray-100">
              <span class="text-text">Reddit Ads</span>
              <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-navy">$400</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm py-2 border-b border-gray-100">
              <span class="text-text">Newsletter sponsorships (2x)</span>
              <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-navy">$500</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm py-2 border-b border-gray-100">
              <span class="text-text">Micro-influencer post (1x)</span>
              <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-navy">$300</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-muted"><strong class="text-navy">Strategy:</strong> Broader content foundation, two paid channels running consistently, and social proof from newsletter and influencer placements.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-6">
          <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-navy">$5,000/mo Stack</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted mt-1">Series A growth</p>
          <div class="mt-6 space-y-3">
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm py-2 border-b border-gray-100">
              <span class="text-text">SEO content (4 posts)</span>
              <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-navy">$1,600</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm py-2 border-b border-gray-100">
              <span class="text-text">Bing Ads</span>
              <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-navy">$800</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm py-2 border-b border-gray-100">
              <span class="text-text">Reddit Ads</span>
              <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-navy">$500</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm py-2 border-b border-gray-100">
              <span class="text-text">Quora Ads</span>
              <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-navy">$400</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm py-2 border-b border-gray-100">
              <span class="text-text">Newsletter sponsorships (3x)</span>
              <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-navy">$800</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm py-2 border-b border-gray-100">
              <span class="text-text">Micro-influencer posts (2x)</span>
              <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-navy">$500</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm py-2 border-b border-gray-100">
              <span class="text-text">Podcast sponsorship (1x)</span>
              <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-navy">$400</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-muted"><strong class="text-navy">Strategy:</strong> Full diversified stack. Three paid platforms, strong content engine, and multiple distribution channels. No single channel accounts for more than 35% of spend.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="max-w-3xl mt-16">

        <!-- RENT VS OWN -->
        <h2 class="font-headline text-3xl font-bold text-navy">The "Rent vs Own" Argument</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-text leading-relaxed">
          Every paid ad is rented attention. The moment you stop paying, the leads stop coming. That's not inherently bad — sometimes you need speed, and renting is the fastest way to get in front of buyers. But if rented channels are 100% of your lead generation strategy, you're building on sand.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-text leading-relaxed">
          Owned channels — your website content, your email list, your LinkedIn audience, your SEO rankings — are assets that compound over time. A blog post that ranks #1 for a high-intent keyword drives free leads every single month. An email list of 5,000 engaged subscribers is a direct line to buyers that no algorithm change can take away.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-text leading-relaxed">
          The smartest marketing strategies use paid channels to learn fast and drive short-term results while simultaneously building owned channels that reduce dependency on paid over time. Here's what that looks like in practice:
        </p>

        <div class="mt-8 space-y-4">
          <div class="bg-light rounded-xl p-5 border border-gray-100">
            <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center gap-3">
              <span class="font-mono font-bold text-orange text-sm">Months 1-3</span>
              <p class="text-text text-sm">70% paid / 30% organic. Use paid to test messages, audiences, and offers. Start building content foundation.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-light rounded-xl p-5 border border-gray-100">
            <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center gap-3">
              <span class="font-mono font-bold text-orange text-sm">Months 4-6</span>
              <p class="text-text text-sm">50% paid / 50% organic. Organic traffic starts contributing. Double down on content that's ranking. Scale winning paid campaigns.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-light rounded-xl p-5 border border-gray-100">
            <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center gap-3">
              <span class="font-mono font-bold text-orange text-sm">Months 7-12</span>
              <p class="text-text text-sm">30% paid / 70% organic. Organic pipeline is now a reliable lead source. Paid focuses on scaling winners and testing new channels.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-light rounded-xl p-5 border border-gray-100">
            <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center gap-3">
              <span class="font-mono font-bold text-orange text-sm">Month 12+</span>
              <p class="text-text text-sm">Your blended cost per lead drops significantly as organic compounds. Paid is now strategic, not essential. You own more than you rent.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-10 bg-orange/5 rounded-xl p-6 border border-orange/10">
          <p class="text-text leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-navy">The bottom line:</strong> The goal isn't to eliminate paid channels — it's to reduce your dependency on any single one. Build a diversified stack where no single channel controls your pipeline, and invest consistently in owned assets that compound over time.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ -->
        <div class="mt-16">
          <FAQSection faqs={faqs} heading="Lead Generation Questions" />
        </div>
